    <h1>Work for the Lord, Not Applause</h1>
    <p class="meta">Oct 20, 2025 ‚Ä¢ ~2‚Äì3 min read</p>

    <p>There are two kinds of people in this world: complainers and doers. You fail a test. You get overlooked for a promotion. You face rejection when you know you gave it your all. What happens next defines who you are ‚Äî not the setback itself.</p>

    <p>Vent if you need to, but don‚Äôt camp there. Lift your head. <strong>Next play.</strong> Didn‚Äôt get the raise? <em>Good.</em> Didn‚Äôt get the promotion? <em>Good.</em> Now show up ten times harder. Be so excellent, so consistent, so committed that no one can ignore you.</p>

    <blockquote>‚ÄúWhatever you do, work at it with all your heart, as working for the Lord, not for men.‚Äù ‚Äî <em>Colossians 3:23</em></blockquote>

    <p>Don‚Äôt drift through life on autopilot, waiting for luck to land on you. There is no luck ‚Äî only preparation meeting purpose. If you want something, go after it. Your mind is powerful; keep it fixed on where you‚Äôre going. As Napoleon Hill said, ‚ÄúWhatever your mind can conceive and believe, it can achieve.‚Äù</p>

    <p>The world talks about ‚Äúbalance,‚Äù but growth rarely comes from comfort. Refinement doesn‚Äôt happen on the mountaintop ‚Äî it happens in the valley. That‚Äôs where grit is born, where faith is forged, and where character is built.</p>

    <blockquote>‚ÄúTrust in the Lord with all your heart, and lean not on your own understanding.‚Äù ‚Äî <em>Proverbs 3:5</em></blockquote>

    <p>My prayer lately is simple: <em>Father, don‚Äôt let me go anywhere You haven‚Äôt gone before me. Walk with me through the journey.</em> It sounds beautiful ‚Äî until His plans stretch you, challenge you, or hold you still. But that‚Äôs where transformation begins.</p>

    <div class="pull">Learn to be comfortable in the uncomfortable. If you want to change the world, you must learn to shine even in your darkest moments.</div>

    <p>Look in the mirror and ask yourself: <strong>Am I a doer, or am I making this all about me?</strong> Then lace up, show up, and get back in the arena.</p>

